# TaskFlow

A full-stack task management app with drag-and-drop boards, priority labels, and category filtering.

Built with **React · Node.js · Express · PostgreSQL**

---

## Features

- Create, complete, and delete tasks
- Drag-and-drop to reorder tasks
- Priority levels: High, Medium, Low
- Categories: Work, Personal, Study, Health
- Filter by status and priority
- Live stats dashboard
- REST API backend with PostgreSQL

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Node.js v18+
- PostgreSQL running locally

### Install & Run

```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Set your database URL (or use the default)
export DATABASE_URL=postgresql://localhost:5432/taskflow

# Start the server
npm run dev
```

Then open `index.html` in your browser, or serve it with any static file server.

### API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | /api/tasks | Get all tasks |
| POST | /api/tasks | Create a task |
| PATCH | /api/tasks/:id | Update a task |
| PATCH | /api/tasks/reorder | Reorder tasks |
| DELETE | /api/tasks/:id | Delete a task |

---

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: HTML, CSS, Vanilla JS (React version in `/client`)
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express
- **Database**: PostgreSQL
- **Deployment**: Render

